The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of end-to-end training and optimization for a specific loss function suggests that this paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of pooling layers and trainable filters suggests that this paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of multi-modal input scans, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
